We anticipate this will take only a few minutes to perform, however the forums and modx.com will be down for a period of hopfully no longer than an hour but likely 30 minutes.";s:14:"date_timestamp";i:1366103869;}i:4;a:9:{s:5:"title";s:78:"Revolution 2.2.7 Out Now—Large Site Scaling Improvements, UI Improvements ++";s:4:"link";s:132:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/modx-announce/~3/REmOigvH_gI/revolution-2-2-7-out-now-large-site-scaling-improvements-ui-improvements";s:11:"description";s:1866:"Today we released MODX Revolution 2.2.7. It&#039;s a jam-packed patch release that includes more than 170 fixes and improvements over 2.2.6. Wowza!<br />
<br />
Revo 2.2.7 includes a new setting (cache_alias_map) to turn off the mapping which caches URLs. This change enables sites with high numbers of resources to perform significantly better. With the new setting left on (business as usual) a site with 100k Resources might consume more than 130Mb of memory on each request; switch it off, and it only uses 24Mb. Additionally, there are many improvements to the user experience and interface in general, along with several other performance enhancements.<br />
<br />
This release does include security fixes. We always recommend upgrading to the latest version of Revolution to keep your MODX sites safe.<br />
<br />
Here are the highlights of the 2.2.7 release:<br />
<ul class="dis-ul"><br />
<li>New index improves performance related to Template Variables and large datasets.</li>
<li>Added support for HttpOnly session cookies for PHP 5.2+ (Security improvement)</li>
<li>Various bug fixes with auto publishing and server_offset_time</li>
<li>Massive scalability improvement for sites with 1000s of Resources by making the aliasMap optional</li>
<li>Allow Elements to be duplicated from the Edit View</li>
<li>A great number of manager UX and code improvements</li>
<li>For more details read the <a href="https://raw.github.com/modxcms/revolution/v2.2.7-pl/core/docs/changelog.txt" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">complete changelog</a></li>
</ul>
<br />
<a href="http://modx.com/download/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Download Revolution 2.2.7 now</a> or read the <a href="http://modx.com/blog/2013/04/09/revolution-2.2.7-large-site-scaling-improvements-and-much-more/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">complete announcement details</a> at the MODX Blog.";s:8:"comments";s:124:"http://forums.modx.com/thread/83760/revolution-2-2-7-out-now-large-site-scaling-improvements-ui-improvements#dis-post-462315";s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Tue, 09 Apr 2013 05:16:51 +0000";s:4:"guid";s:124:"http://forums.modx.com/thread/83760/revolution-2-2-7-out-now-large-site-scaling-improvements-ui-improvements#dis-post-462315";s:10:"feedburner";a:1:{s:8:"origlink";s:124:"http://forums.modx.com/thread/83760/revolution-2-2-7-out-now-large-site-scaling-improvements-ui-improvements#dis-post-462315";}s:7:"summary";s:1866:"Today we released MODX Revolution 2.2.7. It&#039;s a jam-packed patch release that includes more than 170 fixes and improvements over 2.2.6. Wowza!<br />
<br />
Revo 2.2.7 includes a new setting (cache_alias_map) to turn off the mapping which caches URLs. This change enables sites with high numbers of resources to perform significantly better. With the new setting left on (business as usual) a site with 100k Resources might consume more than 130Mb of memory on each request; switch it off, and it only uses 24Mb. Additionally, there are many improvements to the user experience and interface in general, along with several other performance enhancements.<br />
<br />
This release does include security fixes. We always recommend upgrading to the latest version of Revolution to keep your MODX sites safe.<br />
<br />
Here are the highlights of the 2.2.7 release:<br />
<ul class="dis-ul"><br />
<li>New index improves performance related to Template Variables and large datasets.</li>
<li>Added support for HttpOnly session cookies for PHP 5.2+ (Security improvement)</li>
<li>Various bug fixes with auto publishing and server_offset_time</li>
<li>Massive scalability improvement for sites with 1000s of Resources by making the aliasMap optional</li>
<li>Allow Elements to be duplicated from the Edit View</li>
<li>A great number of manager UX and code improvements</li>
<li>For more details read the <a href="https://raw.github.com/modxcms/revolution/v2.2.7-pl/core/docs/changelog.txt" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">complete changelog</a></li>
</ul>
<br />
